FBIS4-11100 "drlat078_b_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 Haiti Constitutionalist Bloc Works on Amnesty Law Constitutionalist Bloc Works on Amnesty Law FL2104195794 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 GMT 21 Apr 94 FL2104195794 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Text] Constitutionalist Bloc senators are now working on the amnesty law. According to parliamentary sources, the Senate office of President Jean-Louis was able to reach the quorum of 13 senators to discuss this law. Alliance [for Parliamentary Cohesion] senators, notably including Franck Leonard and Luc Fleurinord, allegedly participated in those sessions. Senate President Firmin Jean-Louis, who has just returned from a tour of North America, where he met with President Aristide and State Department officials, is working feverishly to finalize the works. The Senate will hold a session this morning in the presence of the press under the presidency of Honorable Firmin Jean-Louis.
